Billions of dust particles across our Solar System scatter the light of the sun and become visible as a huge halo of light called "Zodiacal light". From the shore of Laguna Verde, Atacama desert, Chile, the zodiacal light is so bright that it reflects perfectly into these pristine waters. #desiertodeatacama #atacama #desert #lagunaverde #lagoon #vialactea #milkywaychasers #nightphotography #universe #reflections #astronomy #chile #marcachile

Road to the stars. A desert road in a plateau at 4600 meters of altitude seems to take you directly to the light of billions of stars. Another stunning landscape of Atacama desert.  #desiertodeatacama #cordillera #milkyway #vialactea #road #silence #mountains #universe #atacama #chile #starlight #copiapó

The Milky Way is setting but before disappearing below the horizon gave me a last, amazing glance of its beauty. The reflection into an high altitude lagoon in the heart of the Atacama desert. The sky was all around me and I was feeling great. #milkywaychasers #milkyway #vialactea #salarmaricunga #maricunga #atacama #cordillera #desiertodeatacama #reflections #marcachile #chile #copiapo

Reflections.
In the Atacama desert the Milky Way is so bright that you can easily see it reflected into a normal glass. The sky above and below you, this is truly amazing. #vialactea #desiertodeatacama #marcachile #milkywayreflections #milkyway #reflections #stars #atacama #sonya7s #samyang12mmfisheye

There is nothing more incredible than the Milky Way seen from the Atacama desert. Stars, nebulas, planets and a little of dust of our solar system that merge perfectly to create an amazing view. #desiertodeatacama #vialactea #milkyway #marcachile #atacama #stars #nightsky #amazingsky #universe #astronomy #astronomia

Strange couple. A guanaco wants to play with a desert fox but its curiosity doesn't seem corresponded! #desiertodeatacama #guanaco #zorro #marcachile #cordillera #chile #desert #nature #animals #naturaleza #natgeo

Can you recognize the constellations? Total solar eclipse of July 2nd 2019, Chile. The Sun disappear, the sky gets dark and around it appear the stars. In this photo there are some of the most known constellations of the sky and also three planets. Can you find them all? #eclipse #eclipsesolar #atacama #marcachile #desiertodeatacama #2july #planets #constellations #blacksun #sol #luna #astronomy

Centaurus A, an amazing elliptical galaxy with a huge dust band crossing its center. One of the most spectacular galaxies of the sky.
#centaurus #galaxy #desiertodeatacama #desierto #deepsky #southernsky #universe #astronomy

The Orion nebula is setting behind the dry rocks of the Atacama desert. Such a lovely view. #orion #desiertodeatacama #desierto #sonya7s #marcachile #moonlight #stars #universe #nebula #nebulosa #atacama

Eclipse!
The most amazing show of Nature never disappoints. It was my 4th total eclipse, but the feelings were the same of the first one. When the day turns night you can just stay still, screaming your joy to the sky . Two minutes seem 2 seconds and you will wait for the next one, again and again.

Fireflies in Italian countryside. The early summer nights are the best to see the universe and the nature, communicating in a unique way. #italia #umbria #luciernagas #lucciole #verano #summer #peace

Driving to the stars in the Atacama desert under the moonlight. An amazing feeling! #atacama #desiertodeatacama #desierto #chile #vialactea #estrellas #luna #moonlight #milkyway #milkywaychasers #nightphotography #astronomy

A lens ball in an alien world. In the heart of the Atacama desert, where the silence is the perfect soundtrack for the Universe above you, at the boundary of thick salty crust, so white that seems ice. The Milky Way is rising and you ask to yourself if you are still on Earth of in another, strange, planet. #desiertodeatacama #desierto #atacama #milkywaychasers #nightphotography #marcachile #salar #maricunga #copiapo #vialactea #alienworld #lensball #stars #astronomy #astronomia

Do you not believe that Atacama is the driest desert on Earth? Well, this is the proof! The most recent sign of "heavy" rain is from 2015, 4 years ago! Since then, only few drops of water and the soil shows its thirsty in this picture. #desiertodeatacama #desierto #marcachile #milkywaychasers #night_excl #night #milkyway #vialactea #atacama #sonya7s #samyang12mm #darksky

The Milky way and an ancient salt lake. Seems snow but it's salt and it is so thick that you can actually walk and jump on it. But you need to be careful to the puddles of water. Luckily the Milky Way is so bright that you can notice them by simply looking for the stars reflected below your feet! #desiertodeatacama #atacama #marcachile #milkyway #vialactea #astronomia #reflections #maricunga #salar #chile #beautifulchile #sonya7s

The center of the Milky Way is rising and is reflecting into the pristine waters of a lagoon in the Atacama desert. In the heart of Laguna Nebula, a giant emission nebula that is generating dozens of new stars (and maybe planets). This real color image shows the amazing hues of the Universe. Too faint for the human eye, not for a photographic camera.
